It seemed to be a different way of telling a story, the way it was written. There were parts of it where you figured out the characters were not really real. The story is about a young girl who is trying to remember what happened to her after an accident with a head memory that gave her memory loss and PTSD. Her mother has told family members not to talk to her about the incident. The girl and her mother go back to place the accident happens to spend time and as her memory comes back, she realizes that things that happened were a bigger tragedy than she thought. As I said, IMO, a very different way of telling the story. Quick read and very interesting. Could not put it down. ...more

review: **spoiler alert** This is one of the best books I've read in a long time. It had so much heart. This author is very good at that. This is a story abou**spoiler alert** This is one of the best books I've read in a long time. It had so much heart. This author is very good at that. This is a story about a man named Nathan who finds a new born baby abandoned in the woods while he is duck hunting. The baby is eventually given to his grandmother who names him Nathan but calls him Nat. As the child grows up he becomes hostile and his grandmother has many problems with him. She ends up giving the young boy to Nathan, the man, because she can't control him and she thinks Nathan can help him. The story goes through the life and relationship of this man and the boy as he grows up into a man. It takes a while for the young one to realize that older Nathan is just trying to help him but under the guidance he finally grows up into a substantial person and starts to understand everything that has happened to him. This is a story of love and devotion. This man gave his whole life to this young man because he felt like that was what he was led to do, even gave up his marriage but he was always there for him. LIke I said this story has so much heart and I could not put it down until I finished....more

review: I loved this book. It was a great love story and much more. This one gave me such good feelings the whole time I was reading it, really more than her I loved this book. It was a great love story and much more. This one gave me such good feelings the whole time I was reading it, really more than her big hit book. The story is called confess because everyone in the book has a confession to make. The two young people who fall in love both have confessions and then others in their life do too, such as father of the young man. A young woman meets an artist whose studio is down the street from where she lives and they have immediate attraction. This artist has seen this young woman in the past and does not want to tell her their connection and feels he never can. The connection has to do with her young boyfriend and also father of her son, who died and this young man, Owen, had crossed paths with him while he was in the hospital dying and they had a pact which he never wanted Auburn to know. This is a feeling good love story but there are lots of twists and turns in the story as some of the confessions are revealed. Definitely recommend....more

review: This was an excellent book, very good story. I loved the main character, May (Mae) and the two men she worked for. The only reason I"m giving it 4 staThis was an excellent book, very good story. I loved the main character, May (Mae) and the two men she worked for. The only reason I"m giving it 4 stars instead of 5 is because this book has one of my "pet peeves", no chapters. Second book in a row with no chapters. It's so hard to be able to stop reading! This young woman got a job in an antique store after she had been involved in a scandal and a stay in a mental hospital. She had to move back to Boston from NYC to live with her mother again. But the antique store was a very enlightening experience for her. This is not one of those books where she meets someone wonderful and lives happily ever after but is a story about her learning to figure out her life and the finale was that she found out one of her friends was safe and sound away from Boston. I definitely recommend if you want a "feel good" book for women....more

review: This book turned out to be better than i thought it would be. I didn't enjoy it at first. So many books about missing sisters and so many books with bThis book turned out to be better than i thought it would be. I didn't enjoy it at first. So many books about missing sisters and so many books with back and forth time periods. By the end of the book I ended up really liking it. The sister was not actually missing. She was diagnosed as a psychopath and her younger sister had seen her kill many people who resulted in the younger sister being commited to a mental hospital. When she decides to get out and go home, that's when things really start happening between her and her crazy sister. She does get redemption. The back and forth time line was between the young sister in the mental hospital telling about what's going on with her in the present and ther other time period is the mother telling what happened in the past to lead to her older daughter being diagnosed as a psychopath. There is a crazy aunt in her also. All in all by the end I really like this story and will definitely read more by this author....more

review: I won this book and although I'm not a big Chick Lit fan, this sounded like an interesting story and I enjoyed reading it. The main character is a womI won this book and although I'm not a big Chick Lit fan, this sounded like an interesting story and I enjoyed reading it. The main character is a woman in her 30's who is a school teacher and has been in an extended relationship with a man who is a writer and has started writing hit TV shows. When she watched the shows, she realizes he is uses scenes from her own life in the show and she gets so mad at him, she breaks up with him. Then she begins to realize that if is using things in her life in the show, he is probably using things from his life also and she starts to investigate along with a mutual friend and finds out much more. Then of course, she falls in love with the friend who is helping her. It's a really cute, good story and I enjoyed it....more

It a historic story of a women involved in the witch trials of early Boston when it was first getting started as a city and IMO their very bizarre religious beliefs. The main character who was tried as a witch and broken out of jail by her friends had all of her problems based on a three tined fork which was believe to be from the devil. Author did a lot of research to write this book and I did enjoy it and learned a lot....more

review: I really like this Author. I've read several of her books. They're all mystery/thrillers which are my favorite. This book was an easy and quick read aI really like this Author. I've read several of her books. They're all mystery/thrillers which are my favorite. This book was an easy and quick read and I could not put it down I was so enthralled with the story. It kept changing and you never knew "who did it". She also uses short chapters which I love because to me, it's easier to keep reading and reading. It's a story about a wealthy family and the parents are murdered leaving three adult children to fight over their estate and the police to investigate what happened. There are other family members involved and it seemed to me as I finished the book (and if someone else who read this, has another idea let me know). It seemed that no one was every punished for the crime becaue police had no positive evidence. So, I greatly enjoyed this story and will read more of this author's books....more

review: I really wanted to read this book and did finish it but the first half of the book was very hard for me. This is a book that has an Apple TV+ series bI really wanted to read this book and did finish it but the first half of the book was very hard for me. This is a book that has an Apple TV+ series based on it and it looks really good so I wanted to read the book before I started the series. LIke I said, the first half of the book was very hard for me. The book is not long, but the chapters are, and in the beginning it's hard to get into the main story because the author is telling us everything going on with all the characters. The "slow horses" work at Slough House which is where spys who have gotten in trouble are sent to work. They are easily bored because they don't do much but look at paper and computer. Someone in the group plans a crime and it's a hoax but it takes everyone a while to figure this out. The story got pretty good in the second half, I guess because we were already introduced to all the characters involved. I will try another book in this series and see if I enjoy it more....more

review: I am only giving this 3 stars because I never really understood the book. It is dystopian, but never could figure out whether things were happening inI am only giving this 3 stars because I never really understood the book. It is dystopian, but never could figure out whether things were happening in the past or the future. I am watching the Amazon series hoping it will explain things better but so far not sure. It is a story about women & girls who are given all the power in the world because they develop this special ability to give an electric shock to people whenever they want. There's lots of references to the Bible and i did not understand that completely ever. So, it's a good story, well written with very good characters but confusing. Do recommend that you try this book if you enjoy this type of reading....more

review: Only 3 stars. I really like this author. I've read almost everything she's written and they're always good but this was a strange story in the way it Only 3 stars. I really like this author. I've read almost everything she's written and they're always good but this was a strange story in the way it was told. I read s on here of the book before I read it and I agree with most of the ones I read. This is a story of 6 adults and 3 children being at a barbeque in one of the couple's backyards and something happens that changes all of them forever. You don't find out what it is until you are over half way finished with the book. In the beginning, there was a chapter about the present, then it went to one about the day of the barbeque and it kept going like this all the way through. You found out a little bit more about the day in every other chapter. Then when you find out what happened, you find out about something else that happened on the same day and no one knew it was related. Very interesting story but it took a while to read. I liked the characters but it was trying just figuring out what was going on....more

review: I finished this book last night and really enjoyed it. It was a quick read and very interesting story. My Mystery book club read it as the October choI finished this book last night and really enjoyed it. It was a quick read and very interesting story. My Mystery book club read it as the October choice and we met last night, had a very good discussion about the book and everyone at meeting gave it 4 stars. We all really enjoyed it. To me it was an Agatha Christie type story where you were left hanging at the end of every chapter and you wanted to keep reading to find out what was happening. The ending was a surprise and we never knew "we done it" untli the very end. Definitely recommend and will be reading more books by this author....more

review: I guess I fall with the majority on this, I loved this book. It gave me such a "feel good" feeling. I liked all the characters and many times I found I guess I fall with the majority on this, I loved this book. It gave me such a "feel good" feeling. I liked all the characters and many times I found myself laughing out loud at something that was happening. This is the story of a female chemist back in the 1950's when women were expected to stay home and be housewives and this woman rebelled. Her partner in this, a male chemist was very supportive and then he was killed in an accident and she had to go on without him and a daughter she never really wanted but of course formed a close bond with her. She was fired from her job as a chemist and ended up doing a cooking show on TV where she taught women to combine cooking with chemistry. It was a big hit. Many things happened, she became friends with several people who helped her and she ended up back working at the chemistry lab where she was fired. Like a I said, a very "feel good story". ...more

It was slow moving and mostly consisted of correspondenThis book was a good surprise for me because in the beginning I did not think I would like it. It was slow moving and mostly consisted of correspondence between two of the main characters but then it picked up and ended up really like the story. The author's writing is excellent and she makes you care about of the characters, there are 3 main characters and quite a few secondary. This is the story about a black man falsely imprisoned for a crime he did not commit and what happens to his life while he's in prison and after he gets how and sometimes goes back to his life before prison when he was doing really good. It is also a love story between the three main characters, two men who are friends and the woman they were both in a relationship, and how sometimes love can turn into friendship. I really liked how the story ended and will definitely read more from this author. This story takes place in Atlanta which is where I live and love so that definitely made it better....more

review: I loved this story. It was beautifully written and I love the characters. It is a psychological story about the people we are involved with and the seI loved this story. It was beautifully written and I love the characters. It is a psychological story about the people we are involved with and the secrets they hide. The Divorce Party is about a couple who are divorcing and throw a party to celebrate. Their two children are there with their significant others and plenty of their friends. The husband is hiding a secret, the wife is hiding a secret and their son is hiding a secret. The mother and the son's giflfriend bond of his secret which they have shared and try to understand. The girlfriend was my favorite character in the book and she is an outsider looking in as she had never meet any of this people before the party. She had the boyfriend do reconnect after he shares his secret with her. And this is also the story of a home which was handed down through several generations. At the end the young couple of talking about some of the things they love about the home and they decide to take a bench away and put it in front of the restaurant they are starting. While looking at the bench the young woman discovers a plaque underside of the bench and you found out the son's grandparents put it there, and it is a Van Morrison song which is so appropriate for this story. Loved this! ...more

review: I read the book and watched the movie on Amazon Prime. I must say the book was better than the movie. The movie was like a highlight of the book. The I read the book and watched the movie on Amazon Prime. I must say the book was better than the movie. The movie was like a highlight of the book. The story is about an incident where two men buy gifts from Tiffany's and the gifts gets exchanged in an accident. They go to the wrong person and lots happens after that. The book had a lot of surprising twists and turns, the movie not so many and it did not even end the same. The book had a surpise ending, the movie had an expected ending. As I said I did enjoy the book a lot it was like a romantic comedy with lots of twists and turns. I definitely recommend if you are looking for a good story about love and Christmas in New York City....more

review: Very interesting and different story. I enjoyed reading the book and look forward to watching the series on Hulu. This is the story about a divorce anVery interesting and different story. I enjoyed reading the book and look forward to watching the series on Hulu. This is the story about a divorce and what happened to the people afterward. It's also about how women feel like they are always "less" than men and don't know how to change it. A young doctor is left by his wife with his children and his job and how to juggle all this with the idea of meeting new women because he is single Both parties have lots of resentments and also reconnect with some of their friends from college who try to help them. It took me a while to read this book. It is not divided into chapters and there are lots of words to absorb on each page. But I did enjoy the story....more

review: **spoiler alert** This was an ARC that I won recently and I was pleasantly surprised at how good this book was and how much the story matched up with **spoiler alert** This was an ARC that I won recently and I was pleasantly surprised at how good this book was and how much the story matched up with what is going on in our country today. I have read a few more books by this author but after this one I will read more. The story starts out slow and Sugar and Salt are the names of a adjoining restaurant and bakery in San Francisco. The owner of the restaurant has moved there and started the business to make a big change in her life. We don't learn what happened to her until she falls for the owner of the bakery and she tells him her story and it is sad. She was in jail for shooting the man who raped and attacked her. She fought him and eventually he as shot and killed. He was the son of a very prominent family in the county and they were determined to destroy her. While in jail she found out she was pregnant by the rapist and she tried to get an abortion and the courts, because of the family, drug things out until it was too late for this. She knew she could not have the child of the man who attacked so she gave the baby up for adoption to a wonderful family. While going through all this she became involved with several advocacy groups that really helped her. This is a good story with wonderful characters. definitely recommend....more

review: **spoiler alert** This was a wonderful story that needed to be told. It was a hard to read and I could only read so much of it at one time. It was not**spoiler alert** This was a wonderful story that needed to be told. It was a hard to read and I could only read so much of it at one time. It was not one of those stories where you felt good at the end of the mystery was solved, although the main characters did end up in a good situation but it took so much time. AS most people know about this book by now, this is a story of a woman and her child trying to get across the border from Mexico to America and what they went through. Very hard to read. As someone who was in Mexico a lot when I was younger, this was very interesting to me. It was in the 1980's that I was there a lot and it was nothing then like it is now. I loved the Mexican people and their culture and was so happy to make friends with so many of them. But this woman had to get away because her whole family was killed and she knew she would be next. I definitely recommend this book to everyone. ...more

review: This was a really wonderful true love story. Patti Callahan did a lot of research to write this book and I was very impressed. I have seen both moviesThis was a really wonderful true love story. Patti Callahan did a lot of research to write this book and I was very impressed. I have seen both movies based on the lives of these two people and enjoyed them both. And after reading notes at back of the book written by author I saw that this woman's son had something to do with production of both movies. I loved that too. The face that these two came together and became a family for her two sons who thrived under the fact of living with Mr. Lewis is a great love story in itself but then the one between these two people who really understand each other is amazing and wonderful. I loved this book. It made me feel so good. Also a friend sent me this book because she thought I would enjoy it and I must say, she knows me well. Definitely recommend. Can't wait to read another book by this author. review: Another really good and uplifting story. I won this book but would have picked it out anyway because anytime there is the word "book" in a title, I wiAnother really good and uplifting story. I won this book but would have picked it out anyway because anytime there is the word "book" in a title, I will read the book! LOL. This is a story about a woman who was a prisoner in a camp during WWII. She was Jewish. Her husband and her son died but she survived and moved to Australia to open a bookshop. There she meets and falls in love with a man whose wife left him and went to live at a Jesus Camp. He was devastated and so she was she but they came together and started a wonderful life of ups and downs. The story does have a happy ending and it is a feel good book but it does go back and forth in time with the back story of the concentration camp. Definitely recommend....more

review: **spoiler alert** Very interesting book. Compare to stories by Isabel Allende, magical realism at it's best. Lots of it. This was a question on Jeopar**spoiler alert** Very interesting book. Compare to stories by Isabel Allende, magical realism at it's best. Lots of it. This was a question on Jeopardy two nights ago. What type of writing is Isabel Allende know for - magical realism. This is a story about Orquidea who was a grandmother who had made a deal with a type of man who was a "shining star" and with this deal for his freedom she could have anything she wanted. She called all her relatives to her home when she knew she was dying but instead of just dying she turned into a huge tree. At the same time some of her grandchildren developed roses and vines growing out of part of their body. One of the granddaughters wanted to try to find out how all this happened to her grandmother and they went on a journey back to Ecuador where it all started. This is not really my favorite kind of book but it was a good read and very well written and loved some of the main characters. Will definitely read more by this author....more

I had read another book by this author "The Accident" and this story seemed too similar, and the book was very long! But I stuck with it because it was the book club choice and I ended up really enjoying it. The main part of the story takes place over two nights in Lisbon, of course, and goes into great detail about everything that happens when this woman's husband is supposedly kidnapped. As you keep reading, you find out there's much more going on than that and all types of law enforcement are involved and they can't figure out what's really going on either. the Epilogue at the end finally tells you everything and I ended up pretty satisfied with the story. This is a real thriller and I definitely recommend if you like this kind of book....more

review: Another really good story by David Baldacci. This series' main character is a female FBI agent and she's very likeable. There are two plots going on iAnother really good story by David Baldacci. This series' main character is a female FBI agent and she's very likeable. There are two plots going on in this story and of course they end up being connected. Atless, the FBI female, is looking for her missing sister who was kidnapped years ago by a supposed gangster or his brother. So years later she is looking for the brother who is also missing. There is another crime connected with the gangster people that she becomes involved in because of this search. The reason I gave this 4 stars instead of 5 is because I did not feel that she ever resolved what happened to her sister. She found some pictures and a VCR tape and also found a lot more information about her parents and the missing gangster but was disappointed because I did not feel the missing sister part of the story was completely resolved. I hope this author continutes this in another book. Will definitely read....more

review: This is a beautifully written story about a very hard subject. Jodi Picoult is one of my favorite writers. I try to read everything she has published.This is a beautifully written story about a very hard subject. Jodi Picoult is one of my favorite writers. I try to read everything she has published. I have even gone and heard her speak in person. Love her and love this book. The subject matter is hard but the way the story is told is what makes it so good. To tell it very quickly, a transgender girl is found dead, her boyfriend is arrester for murdering her, there is a trial, the boyfriend's uncle represents him and his lawyer and he brings in enough medical experts to create doubt in the jurys mind where they find the young man "not guilty". There is a lot of background about the transgender girl and also the family members of both her and the boyfriend. The back story for the girl is very compelling and I actually felt I got to know her and really loved her too. I know this will be a hard book for some to read but I definitely recommend mainly because it is a lovely, well written, story. ...more

This is an unusual story that takes place decades ago when people were just changing from going on Afridan safaris to African photo shoots and they did not want to shoot the animals although there were of course some who always tried. Part of this story is based on Hemingway's life and all the pictures we saw when younger about him on safari with other Hollywood celebrities. But there is always discord in Africa and a group of Russian terrorists invaded their camp and took them hostage, killing many along the way. I could not put it down and it's not a short story. I know it has been made into a series on Peacock and I am starting to watch that too. Of course, I saw episode 1 last night and it has already been changed from the book. Don't know why. IMO the book is perfect. On the day the police decide to arrest her husband for murdering her because of circumtantial evidence, the police go to the house and she is there. Then we find out what happened. This story is told in the first person and you never know her real name and the name of most of the characters. But the main character is on the run from her life. She had a baby for her twin sister who could not conceive. Then found out her twin sister was having an affair with her husband. She left her home and went to stay with a friend who was Casablanca and she tells this woman about it and the woman decides she loves the stories on want to go there. So she does, then her backpack is stolen with her passport in it and she travels over the North Africa with no ID using different names and she goes from one adventure to another, even involving a job as a stand in on a movie set. The story was more of a fantasy and I expected reality to step in. I read s on Goodreads before I read the book and it seemed that most people liked it. This is a story about a town that has a spring that people believe have healing waters. I grew up close to Warm Springs, GA where there were warm springs that people believed were healing, even the president of the US and then in a town nearby there was a cold springs, Pine Mountain, and they had a swimming pool fed by this spring and it was wonderful. So I grew up with the healing waters around me and part of my life. But in the book the water were not only healing but they were evil in a way. I had hoped that with the ending it would have a basis for this based on reality but it was fantasy all the way. I wanted the story to make sense in a realistic way but it never did. review: This was an ARC I received from the publisher. There is a warning on the book that the subject matter of the story is very harsh and it is but the wayThis was an ARC I received from the publisher. There is a warning on the book that the subject matter of the story is very harsh and it is but the way the story is written is lovely. The main character, a teenage girl named Roan is wonderful and so brave. The story is about a horse farm and a young girl who wants to ride on the Olympics team, first because she loves horses and second because her father was an Olympic winner. The father is a very controlling man who controls all her life, including having had sex with her since she was a small child. The mother is absent all the time giving the father total custody of her when they divorced. The story is about this young girl being strong enough to stand up to this man who had always abused her and the courage she had. She is a teenager so she meets a boy in school and develops a relationship with him which makes her realize how wrong the relationship with her father is and all she wants to do is put him in his place and she does. LIke I said, a really good story and beautifully written. ...more
